Pantheon Semantic Coordinate Layer
query.py — Four-pass semantic query resolver

Resolution passes:

1. Direct match   — exact node names, aliases, compression phrases
1. Invariant match — nodes sharing similar core invariant
1. Neighborhood expansion — neighbors, opposites, related doctrines
1. Transfer expansion — known mappings into other domains

Silence is a valid state. If no pass finds a stable match,
the resolver returns a structured null result rather than a weak guess.
“””

